Noted should be that the `response.length()` part in their example is bad, it should have been `response.getBytes().length`. Even then, the `getBytes()` method must explicitly specify the charset which you then specify in the response header. Alas, albeit misguiding to starters, it&#39;s after all just a basic kickoff example.

